answers.answer: I haven't dealt with that but I've heard those are extremely common! That lots of babies who show positive for Down's syndrome are born and don't have it. That's why they're supposed to make sure you know it's not 100%.
What made them say that about the preeclampsia ?
The fact that it was a protien in my bloodwork that popped up out of the norm and my pulse is running high.
I believe its pretty common.. all the best :)

Lol they shouldn't worry you like that. EVERY woman's pulse runs high when pregnant, especially if they're nervous, which they usually are at doctors offices. Plus, your heart is working waaay more producing so much more blood. Also, some women have protein in their urine at one appt, and it goes away at the next. I drank a ton of water after having a trace amount of protein come up and it went away. You can have protein from what you ate that day or being dehydrated. The BIGGEST sign of preeclampsia is high blood pressure and extreme swelling.

question: So, we went in for testing on Tuesday for downs syndrome. I was told it was a false positive and we have a beautifully healthy baby by looks of things. Has anyone else had a false positive for downs syndrome? They also said that I am at high risk of preeclampsia. :o
